NOT ANYMORE! 😏 I just gave a whole new look to my dining room using 3M CLAW Drywall Picture Hanger - and let me tell you: I will never go back to hanging my heavy wall decor any other way! If you know me, you know I like to change my decor every so often, so I always avoided hanging heavy objects so that I didn’t have to deal with a huge mess whenever I wanted to switch up my decor! But by using the 3M CLAW Hanger I have the freedom to hang my decor with confidence because I know if I ever want to change it up I will have no large holes left behind! Quick and easy fix! Also, they have sizes that hang up to 65LBS! 😱 How awesome is that?! And if that wasn’t enough, it is also extremely easy to install. No tools or stud needed! Just push the hanger into your drywall with your thumbs and you are all set! 🙌 I don’t know about you, but I’m SOLD! Since I was on my “WHAT CAN I CHANGE IN THIS HOUSE” mood, I also went ahead and switched up my side entrance wall decor by using Command Picture Hanging Strips. Fun fact: I use Command for all my wall decor under 20lbs because I can remove it at any time with no damage to my walls.

Here’s how I made my dream gallery wall come true on plaster walls (and they work on drywall too).  What are your fave hanging methods? 

Besides the magical 3M velcro strips, I used ‘plaster picture hangers’ and ‘monkey hooks’.

You don’t even need any tool for monkey hooks, just wiggle them through. Yes, even on plaster (though you could drill a tiny pilot hole to make it easier). And they hold 100lb. 

The plaster picture hangers just hammer in and hold a variety of weight depending on if they are a single, double or triple nail. 

Here’s what they look like behind the wall using my fancy cardboard mock-up. Don’t forget the poster putty so they don’t shift around.
